Description: Sherd of probably East Greek grey ware small closed pottery vessel, mended from six fragments; polished slip on outside and moulded decoration of palmette.
Bibliographic references: Etruscan Bucchero / A Catalogue of Etruscan Bucchero in the British Museum (No. 309)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.169)
